  "read": "This probe tests whether the local grouped-reduction contract keeps working when expanded from one CTA to a full token/selected/D grid. The optional contrib_sink path computes rocWMMA contribution tiles and writes only one sampled scalar per route tile, so raw_atomic minus contrib_sink approximates the selected-row dKV write path. It also times a direct-fragment contrib sink that reads c_frag[] without store_matrix_sync, which isolates accumulator-spill overhead but does not provide a geometric row/group map for route reduction. It still materializes diagnostic probabilities and grad logits, and can either use grouped global atomics or emit grouped route-tile partials for a separate reduction, so it is a schedule-pressure probe rather than the final fused sparse-MLA/LI backward kernel."
